[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T22:32:53+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Steam Deck on a white and orange background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/OtT4tjmvlAg2oEEzLnY86aJhZVU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291667/vpavic_220210_5030_0090.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Valve says each unit has received over 100 tests and meets the same performance standards as new Steam Decks.</em> | Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wOPoQ2\">It\u2019s not often we see an excellent portable gaming PC like the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23513517/steam-deck-long-term-test-valve\"><strong>Steam Deck</strong></a> on sale for nearly half off, but today\u2019s your lucky day. So long as you don\u2019t mind buying it in certified refurbished condition, you can save hundreds when you purchase it directly (with a one-year warranty included) from Valve right now.</p>\n<p id=\"CqEFkQ\">The refurbished Steam Deck starts at <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/sale/steamdeckrefurbished", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24135233/value-steam-deck-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "You can buy a refurbished Steam Deck for almost half off", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T21:31:52+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of Mario, Yoshi, and other Mario Kart characters driving on a course that resembles a pinball machine.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0ekhPNuM_ePkW77e51A15qZGfLA=/0x0:1620x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291547/Mario_Kart_8_Deluxe_Booster_Course_Pass.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nintendo</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"rnCglk\">If you\u2019re the kind of Mario Kart 8 player who cares about winning and not just playing their favorite characters (Daisy and Peach supremacy), choosing the best combination of driver, vehicle, and wheels gets tricky. </p>\n<p id=\"ywpnQZ\">Luckily, thanks to data science and 19th-century Italian economist Vilfredo Pareto, there\u2019s a way to figure that out. <a href=\"https://www.mayerowitz.io/blog/mario-meets-pareto\">Data scientist Antoine Mayerowitz</a> applies one of Pareto\u2019s principles, the Pareto front, to plot the best combination among the 703,560 possible decisions players must make", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24135206/mario-kart-pareto-front-math-data-peach-rulez", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Applying the mathematical principles of Pareto to Mario Kart 8", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T21:13:14+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"five electric kia vehicles fanned out in a modern architecture area with stone brick flooring\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3XdedyGKD3I1esfMFpfTl1-LeEY=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291500/key_message_03_lg.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Kia\u2019s lineup of electric vehicles are growing.</em> | Image: Kia</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"H2fXTz\">The Kia EV2, the automaker\u2019s small, affordable electric crossover, has been <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/shorts/ch8ULhHAKWg\">spotted on the street in camouflage</a>. It\u2019s the first time the model has been seen in the wild, although the EV2 is not currently confirmed for the US.</p>\n<p id=\"aJrg4S\">The timing of the sighting is particularly significant given recent news that Tesla may <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/5/24122064/tesla-cancel-affordable-electric-vehicle-model-2-china\">have canned its plans</a> for a $25,000 mass-market \u201cModel 2\u201d vehicle. Elon ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24135116/kia-ev2-ev-affordable-cheap-electric-tesla-model-2", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Kia\u2019s more affordable EV2 is getting ready to undercut Tesla", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T21:04:09+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing the exterior of a Target in Texas\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/K8DyAwhxhabgpUKbH7HB5JQD4Lo=/0x17:1000x684/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291482/target_exterior_design.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Target</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"IjfBZ5\">Target is scaling back the presence of physical media in its stores. A <a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/target-will-continue-to-sell-physical-media-in-stores-and-online\">spokesperson for Target tells <em>IGN</em></a> that the company is \u201ctransitioning the limited assortment of DVDs\u201d it sells in stores to its website.</p>\n<p id=\"KUyYGg\">\u201cMoving forward, we\u2019ll offer select DVDs in stores when they are newly released or during key times throughout the year when they are more popular, like for gift giving during the holidays,\u201d Target says. That will make Target\u2019s physical DVD section even smaller and only available during specific times. You\u2019ll still be able to", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24135140/target-dvds-physical-media-selling-stop", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Target confirms it\u2019s all but completely ditching DVDs in physical stores", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T20:20:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo from Phish\u2019s first performance at the Sphere in Las Vegas.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/6dgeVW9B0PrtYeXvBqyLNMm9SGc=/0x1:1800x1201/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291371/PhishSphere2024_0418_225029_0799_ALIVECOVERAGE_Enhanced_NR.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alive Coverage</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Four nights of unique set lists and long jams presented a much different production challenge than U2\u2019s 40-show residency.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24134861/phish-sphere-las-vegas-moment-factory-interview\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24134861/phish-sphere-las-vegas-moment-factory-interview", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Phish turned Las Vegas\u2019 Sphere into the ultimate music visualizer", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T20:08:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Key art from Hades 2 featuring the protagonist Melino\u00eb, a young woman with bicolor eyes and green, glowing arm.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x_WHXZvuDUa2oaDereJb5AlITww=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291335/H2_Wallpaper_Melinoe_4k_01.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Supergiant Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"DC260q\">Imagine the most perfect barbecue \u2014 a prolific spread of smoked meats, all the right sides, every pie, type of cookie or cake, and even your grandmother\u2019s famous dinner rolls. But there\u2019s a catch: most of the food is kept behind glass to be unlocked at a later date, and you are <em>starving</em>. That\u2019s what it\u2019s like playing <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/16/24132188/hell-approacheth\">the <em>Hades 2</em> technical test</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"O46CbD\"><em><strong>Spoilers for the </strong></em><strong>Hades 2 </strong><em><strong>technical test.</strong></em></p>\n<p id=\"Cq9ie0\"><em>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24135151/hades-2-technical-test-impressions", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Hades 2 technical test is a trial in self-control", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T19:15:21+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of the Chromecast with Google TV HD streaming player on a coffee table.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/HzANxAvC8bmGOx-lizXAmHGtIZ8=/0x12:2040x1372/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291185/chromecast.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Google\u2019s latest streaming dongle offers a cheap way to add smart features and apps to any TV.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"g4KW9v\">Almost any TV you can buy these days supports streaming in some form or fashion, but what if you don\u2019t like its user interface or it doesn\u2019t have all of the apps you need? That\u2019s where a streaming device like the <strong>Chromecast with Google TV (HD)</strong> comes in. We usually recommend jumping for <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Google-Nest-GA01919-GA01919-US-Chromecast/dp/B08KRV7S22?tag=theverge02-20\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">the 4K version</a> if you have the budget for it, but the HD model is only $19.99 ($", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134035/google-chromecast-hd-dreamebot-l20-ultra-robot-vacuum-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google\u2019s HD Chromecast is going for just $20", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T18:55:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the logo for Post on a purple background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kGpaG_8DD25_HVtLxrh2f6iS-Hs=/0x343:2057x1714/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291124/post_logo.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Post News</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Mcd1m6\">Post News, a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23494253/elon-musk-twitter-alternatives-mastodon-post-hive-narwhal\">Twitter alternative that emerged</a> in the wake of Elon Musk\u2019s takeover, is shutting down. Noam Bardin, the platform\u2019s founder and former CEO of Waze, <a href=\"https://post.news/@/noam/2fJw4PYRFjya343RpiToiyEQr0x\">writes that Post News</a> \u201cis not growing fast enough to become a real business or a significant platform.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"j3zlKq\">The Andreessen Horowitz-backed platform launched in a closed beta in November 2022, but now it\u2019s set to shutter \u201cwithin the next few weeks.\u201d It serves as a social platform that also offers users ad-free access to ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24135011/twitter-alternative-post-news-shutdown", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Twitter alternative Post News is shutting down", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T18:22:45+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Cartoon image of a robot housekeeper with its family of humans.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qPb9_bEBjNDCYsPi-EqOxXJtvE8=/340x0:1360x680/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73291036/jetsons.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Friend or foe? </em>The Jetsons\u2019<em> Rosey the Robot has long been an inspiration for developing home robots. But should it be?</em> | Image: Warner Bros. Television, Hanna-Barbera</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"RBwHNz\">As a child of the 1980s, my perception of the smart home has been dominated by the idea that one day, we will all have Rosey the Robot-style robots roaming our homes \u2014 dusting the mantelpiece, preparing dinner, and unloading the dishwasher. (That last one is a must; we were smart enough to come up with a robot to wash our dishes; can\u2019t we please come up with one that can also unload them?)</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"2GbkPj\"><div></div></aside></div>\n<p id=\"yV0F13\">How", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134905/boston-dynamics-atlas-robot-smart-home-robot", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Maybe I don\u2019t want a Rosey the Robot after all", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T16:38:23+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Artwork showing the Delta icon and the Apple App Store logo, with screenshots from the emulator.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NjKM2dD4SdcyH9Kd8g4BECQJUYQ=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73290702/delta_app_store.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Riley Testut</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"LF3AkT\">The launch of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/17/24132984/delta-free-emulator-nintendo-gba-n64-iphone-app-store-us\">the Delta emulator on iPhones</a> is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134767/emulators-iphone-delta-google-meta-ai-vergecast-podcast\">a big deal in a lot of ways</a>. But for users, it\u2019s also just <em>really</em> cool. Here\u2019s an excellent piece of software that can emulate the NES, SNES, N64, Game Boy, GBA, and Nintendo DS so that you can play classic games on a device that\u2019s always in your pocket. Even better: even though there\u2019s no Delta app for the Apple TV (yet), it\u2019s still r", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134871/delta-emulator-apple-tv-airplay", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "AirPlay turns the Delta emulator into a full-on retro console", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T15:58:46+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Taylor Swift | The Eras Tour - Singapore\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/uUjRzhNLT0ywCk1rbxtW53XHUz0=/0x0:5103x3402/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73290571/2053045625.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Ashok Kumar / TAS24 / Getty Images for TAS Rights Management</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"PmYTn9\">TikTok has launched a new hub to promote Taylor Swift\u2019s new album where you can earn in-app rewards for completing certain tasks, like following Swift\u2019s account on the platform. The update comes just days after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/11/24127406/taylor-swifts-music-tiktok-umg-deal\">Swift\u2019s music returned to TikTok</a> as the app continues to feud with the singer\u2019s record label, Universal Music Group (UMG).</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\">  <figure class=\"e-image\">\n        \n      <cite>Image: TikTok</cite>\n  </figure>\n</div>\n<p id=\"eccbQT\">You can access the hub by searching for <em>The Tortured Poet", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134795/taylor-swift-ttpd-tiktok-hub-universal-music-group", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Taylor Swift gets custom collab with TikTok as UMG battle continues", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T14:50:36+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"In an aerial view, a recovery vehicle drives past burned structures and cars in a neighborhood next to shoreline.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tj1YiK1pBLYGpc7dzj-SN4KvwJM=/0x15:5017x3360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73290336/1727318537.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>A recovery vehicle drives past burned structures and cars two months after a devastating wildfire on October 9th, 2023, in Lahaina, Hawaii.&nbsp;</em> | Photo by Mario Tama / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Znom0U\">New details surfaced this week about cascading failures that led to wildfires ripping through Maui last August. While investigations confirming the cause of the blaze are ongoing, officials are recognizing how unprepared agencies were for the inferno. </p>\n<p id=\"SmBJG1\">The wildfires killed at least 101 people and scorched some 2,200 structures \u2014 most of them residential. Downed power lines, blocked evacuation routes, and poor communi", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134274/infrastructure-planning-failures-maui-hawaii-wildfire-report", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How planning and infrastructure failed during Maui wildfires", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T14:43:23+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Firefighters spraying a Waymo car.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TyaRgMlZujfAvgcdRs0bCa39tt8=/98x0:2218x1413/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73290324/Screenshot_2024_02_11_at_11.34.11_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Waymo vehicle was set on fire with fireworks.</em> | Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4SJO3EbR-_w\" target=\"_blank\">Frisco Live 415</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZDF4x7\">The San Francisco Police Department has <a href=\"https://www.sanfranciscopolice.org/news/sfpd-autonomous-vehicle-arson-update-24-034\">identified and served a search warrant</a> on a teenager who is suspected of starting a fire in a Waymo self-driving taxi vehicle earlier this year. </p>\n<p id=\"0yuODs\">On March 27th, investigators entered the suspect\u2019s residence and seized evidence that connects the 14-year-old male with <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/11/24069251/waymo-driverless-taxi-fire-vandal", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134801/waymo-fire-arson-san-francisco-teen-police", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "A 14-year-old is charged in fire that destroyed a driverless Waymo vehicle", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T14:02:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of hot air balloons carrying various Mother\u2019s Day gifts.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/drF8sxK2oKQSKl03XYlOd9EAgZ8=/0x0:1750x1167/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73290208/247058_Mothers_Day_Gift_Guide_MLouart.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Manon Louart for The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>We found a collection of unique gift ideas that go beyond the flowers and chocolates that typically rule the day.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24115101/best-mothers-day-gift-ideas-2024-mom-tech-gadgets\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24115101/best-mothers-day-gift-ideas-2024-mom-tech-gadgets", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 100, "page_rating_contents": 100, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Verge\u2019s 2024 Mother\u2019s Day gift guide", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-04-19T12:53:33+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Tesla Cybertruck outside\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0IDu3lfvT01nFiz4XO2FWS9KcwE=/0x168:4032x2856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73289967/IMG_0618.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Tesla isn\u2019t aware of any collisions, injuries, or fatalities attributed to the defective pedals.</em> | Image: Parker Ortolani / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"1zzS8D\">Tesla has issued a recall for effectively every Cybertruck it\u2019s delivered to customers due to a fault that\u2019s causing the vehicle\u2019s accelerator pedals to get stuck. </p>\n<p id=\"yRu9U7\"><a href=\"https://static.nhtsa.gov/odi/rcl/2024/RCLRPT-24V276-7026.PDF\">According to the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration</a> (NHTSA) on Wednesday, the defect can result in the pedal pad dislodging and becoming trapped in the vehicle\u2019s interior trim when \u201chigh force is applied.\u201d</p>\n<p id=\"767G5I\">The fault was caused by an \u201cunapproved change\u201d that introduced \u201clubricant (soap)\u201d ", "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/4/19/24134753/tesla-recall-cybertruck-faulty-accelerator-pedal-nhtsa-defect", "manual_status_c